<br>
1. you have 30 days after they expire before a cop can write you a ticket..if they do you will win in court.<br>
that means if they expiration date is july 2002 you have til august 1st 2002 to put new tags on.<br>
2. no cop EVER would tow your vehicle and leave you standing on the side of the road with no transportation.<br>
1st off that is illegal and that cop would lose his job instantly<br>
and also if you were hit by another car or somehow was hurt by being left on the road the city/county/state police whoever left you there, would be liable for a very huge lawsuit. so guess what? thats 1 of the 1st things you are told when you join the force.<br>
its something cops just plain do not do no matter how big of a asshole they are.<br>
they are required to find you transportation, and if you dont know anyone they call you a cab.<br>
if you cant afford a cab they will aresst you on protective custody take you to the police station then let you go and then they are not liable for you.<br>
but you are correct a policeman cannot give you a ride, its just something they are not allowed to do at all for their own protection.<br>
only time you will see a cop giving a ride would be in a very small 1 cop town where he has knowone to answer to.<br>
3. therefore i come to the conclusion what really happened is you were running on tags that were over 30 days old and the cop ticketed you had your truck towed and called your dad who came and got you, and then your dad paid the 200 bucks to get your truck out of tow since you cant even afford the 35 bucks to renew your tags. and your dad also paid your ticket for you then you had to work it all off by bending over for your dad to rape your sorry lying ass.<br>
sorry wouldnt be a flame if i didnt add some flare at the end =P<br>
